replies.body:
I feel like Riot is slowly creating a "minimum impact" item for every class that just says "Well, even if you screw up everything, at least you have this to boost your damage/durability/impact by X amount."

AD Assassin- {{item:3147}} 
AP Assassin- {{item:3100}} 
Ranged AP Assassin/Mage- {{item:3285}} 
Hybrid Burst- {{item:3146}} 
Solo Tanks- {{item:3193}} 
Enchanters- {{item:3107}} 
Support Tanks- {{item:3190}} 
Bruisers- {{item:3078}} 
Crit Marksman- {{item:3095}} (its still in the process of being forged)
Caster Marksman- {{item:3508}} 
On-hit Carries- {{item:3124}} 

Just hit that active/passive proc, and you have already dealt some decent damage from the source of the proc and the proc itself! Or gained a big boost of durability! Or healed a lot! Whatever! You have this item, so you are instantly improved by a ton even if you suck!
The strengths of these classes basically revolve around the strengths of these items as well as some impact from keystones/runes. It's kind of saddening.

Edit: The more I keep going the more I realize almost every "style of play" has one item that's just like "If you don't buy me, you're playing a weakened version of this character". Of course, you can name 1-3 champions for every class that break these rules, but everyone else? It applies. And you know what!? For those champions that do break the rules, unless they just have some insane other item synergy like Zhonya's champions, they just feel awkward to build.

