Completely agree to this. That being said, LoL is now more or less catered towards a new younger audience, a younger audience who can't maturely deal with their own lack of skill. I remember someone before called it "childproof" in the sense that young children who do miss everything still can feel like they made an impact. LoL needs to be way less forgiving so that plays are actually properly rewarding for the effort used. I really miss the days of being blown away by a pro player making the first 'trademarked' play like the insec kick because LoL was way less forgiving so seeing that pulled off had the most impact. Now everyone can do it, and although it's not a bad thing, the stakes are far FAR lower if you fail it now than before.
